# Auto-Bootstrap & Dependency Reading

## Session Start Bootstrap

At session start or when taking over a task, load the **Core Bootstrap** (3 rules, ~800 tokens) instead of the old Default Bootstrap (12 rules):

1. Read [CORE_BOOTSTRAP.md](../../CORE_BOOTSTRAP.md) — 3 core rules: `rule-weight.md`, `dependency-reading.md`, `conversation-goal-ledger.md`
2. Read [README.md](../../README.md) — OS layout & quickstart
3. Match task intent against [routing-registry.yaml](../../knowledge/runtime/routing-registry.yaml) to find the relevant route
4. Check [runtime/router/activation-rules.yaml](../../runtime/router/activation-rules.yaml) for which lazy-load rules to activate
5. Load Runtime Phase initialization:
   - [runtime/phases/phase-machine.yaml](../../runtime/phases/phase-machine.yaml) — current phase state
   - [runtime/obligations/obligation-ledger.yaml](../../runtime/obligations/obligation-ledger.yaml) — phase obligations
   - [runtime/gates/blocking-gates.yaml](../../runtime/gates/blocking-gates.yaml) — phase blocking gates
6. Load Output Governance initialization:
   - [runtime/output-governance/language-policy.yaml](../../runtime/output-governance/language-policy.yaml) — language enforcement rules
   - [runtime/output-governance/output-rules.yaml](../../runtime/output-governance/output-rules.yaml) — document output rules
   - [runtime/output-governance/governance-gates.yaml](../../runtime/output-governance/governance-gates.yaml) — output quality blocking gates
7. Read the skill's summary from `knowledge/summaries/` (300-500 tokens) before expanding to full source

## Dependency Reading

- If a skill, shared rule, Cursor rule, template, or feedback lesson has changed, will be changed, or affects the task, read the relevant dependent files before concluding or editing.
- Always include `shared-rules/` in that dependency read, especially `shared-rules/dependency-reading.md` and `shared-rules/linked-updates.md`.
- For reusable docs, follow `shared-rules/tool-neutral-documentation.md`: keep root/shared/skill docs tool-neutral and place Cursor-specific paths, hooks, UI, and sync details in `ai-tools/cursor.md` or `.cursor/rules/`.
- For conversation goal tracking, use `shared-rules/conversation-goal-ledger.md`: active user goals belong in project-local `.agent-goals/` temporary state and do not replace the Ai-skill git writeback transaction.
- For skill changes, read the skill entry plus related README, workflow, documentation, checklist, templates, feedback indexes, and linked shared rules when they exist.
- If a dependent file does not exist, mark it as not applicable; do not claim it was checked.
- When a user asks to reload a skill or points out that shared rules may have been missed, create a dependency read ledger before returning to project work: trigger, required set, files read, not-applicable files, deferred/blocked items, and validation method.
- When a user points out a repeated agent mistake, wrong source/mirror update, missed validation, or incomplete close loop, follow `shared-rules/failure-learning-system.md`: classify the failure mode, update the durable prevention target, and validate the new guardrail.
- Do not claim the updated skill has been applied while the ledger still has unread required files that are neither read nor explicitly marked not applicable.
- Before finishing, state the dependency read and validation method: diff review, lints, link check, required linked updates, and tool sync when relevant. Reference-only Cursor usage does not require running bundle sync.
- After `git commit`, `git push`, and any required tool sync, re-read the updated skill/shared-rule entry files and main dependencies so the current agent context reflects the pushed version before the final response.
- On the first write to `shared-rules/`, `skills/`, `.cursor/rules/`, templates, feedback lessons, sync scripts, or their `~/.cursor` synced paths, immediately open an Ai-skill writeback transaction. Do not return to project work or claim completion until diff review, linked updates, required tool sync, commit, push, reread, and clean `git status --short --branch` have closed it.
- Before any final response after writing to this repo, run `git status --short --branch`; if there are modified/untracked/staged files or the branch is ahead/behind remote, do not say the Ai-skill update is complete. Finish validation, sync, commit, push, reread, and confirm clean status first, or explicitly report the blocker.
